  "modName": "Skyrim Optical Enhancement",
  "summary": "Two simple optical enhancements added - lens flare and chromatic aberration",
  "descriptionHtml": "This mod is changes a bit the FXAA Post Process Injector shader, by some_dude (all credits to him). I have added a soft lens flare effect that is applied upon any bright screen. The second thing is the chromatic aberration. Both effects are fully configurable from within the OpticalEnhancement.h file.\r\n\r\nInstallation\r\nYou need the current version of the FXAA Post Process Injector (http://www.skyrimnexus.com/downloads/file.php?id=131)\r\nFirst backup your shader.fx file (if You have been editing it). Next extract the archive to the main Skyrim directory ([steamDir]\\\\SteamApps\\\\common\\\\skyrim\\\\).\r\n\r\nUninstallation\r\nRestore Your backuped shader.fx file and remove OpticalEnhancement.h from the injFX_Shaders subdirectory.\r\n\r\nKnown bugs\r\nThe chromatic aberration is done by scaling the texture coordinates for each color channel separately so it can lead to some color distortion.\r\n\r\nShould You find any bugs or want to discuss the mod, contact me at the Nexus formus.\r\n\r\nBless You,\r\nMK",
